Summary: AM CVns are H-deficient accreting white dwarf binaries with 5<P_orb<70 mins. Recent outbursts observations have demonstrated their unique behavior, challenging traditional accretion models, but their understanding is very limited given the small number of known systems. We propose to perform a TESS survey on 2446 transients classified as "CV candidates" to uncover the hidden population of outbursting AM CVs. We will obtain the best estimate of the AM CVn population density, while studying their outburst characteristics. Our project will provide to the astro-community the largest catalog of CV ligthcurves to be used for observational/theoretical studies.
